{
  "stem": "893.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We got-- they wired the visas to Prague.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in Prague, they arranged for us-- there was a relief organization, Vaad Hatzalah, in the United States, and that was my cousin-- that was founded by my cousin's brother-in-law.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had in place in Prague offices where they were helping people to get out of Russia, Poland-- all these countries.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [INAUDIBLE] they arranged also for us to get-- it was out of question for me to get a Czechoslovakian passport.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They wouldn't let us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They would have wanted us first to serve in their armed forces.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they arranged us to receive iden-- IDs from the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And since we had a destination area where they would-- would take us in, like Tangier, we were able to get transit pass-- visas through Germany from the military authorities, and then transit visas in France and Spain, all the way to Tangier.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And how long did you stay in Tangier?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Tangier, we stayed for two-- two years.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Had we arrived in-- after we arrived in Tangier, the legation wouldn't-- wouldn't give us any American visas unless we have a-- a legitimate passport.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We contacted the consular-- Czechoslovakian consular authorities in London.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They wouldn't-- they would only give us a passport-- I still have it-- to return to Czechoslovakia, but not to-- not to any other country.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It took us till we-- it took us several months to find someone who had some connections with the Moroccan authorities-- French Moroccan authorities-- to give us a stateless passport.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They issued us a stateless passport.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "By the time the passport was issued, the Czechoslovakian quarter was closed, so we couldn't come to the United States on that visa.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we got stuck for two years.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
